This section describes the common functionalities of the Activities, Analytics, Documents, and Invoices services of the Electronic Invoicing and Electronic Ordering Doxee Platform services.

> Note

For more information on the common functionalities of Doxee Platform 3 services, excluding EI-EO services, see: [Doxee Platform 3 Common Functionalities](/doxee-platform/docs/doxee-platform-3-common-functionalities).

## Search filters
The search filter panel allows you to set one or more search parameters, combining fields of different types.

> Note

The following example displays an example of the fields available for the Active Electronic Invoicing service:

![](data:image/png;base64,)

## 
### Search filter tools
![](data:image/png;base64,)

Icon

Action

Description

![](data:image/png;base64,)

**Reset**

Reset all search filters to the default configuration.

![](data:image/png;base64,)

**Configure**

Select the columns to be displayed and define the order in which they appear.

### Applying search filters
- Set the required parameters in the search filters panel on the left. 

- Click **Search**.

> Important

The configured search parameters are not applied in real time to the data displayed in the table. You must click **Search** to start the search.

### Search filter field types
Icon

Field type

Description

![](data:image/png;base64,)

**Text**

Enter a single text string.

![](data:image/png;base64,)

**List**

Enter one or more text strings.

![](data:image/png;base64,)

**Multiple selection**

Select one or more options.

![](data:image/png;base64,)

**Amount range**

Enter a numeric range (From  To).

![](data:image/png;base64,)

**Date**

Select a date or date range:

- Today

- Yesterday

- Last week

- Last month

- Custom range (From  To)

### Configuring search filters
To configure the search filters displayed and the order in which they appear:

- Click ![](data:image/png;base64,). The **Configure Filters **panel appears. For example, for the Electronic Invoicing service:![](data:image/png;base64,)

- Select the checkboxes corresponding to the fields that you wish to display.

- Drag fields to the desired position using the icon ![](data:image/png;base64,).

- Click **Configure** to apply the configuration.

> Tip

Click **Reset** to reset the default fields and the predefined order.

## Configuring a table
To customize the table view and select which columns to display and the order in which they appear, follow these steps: 

- Click ![](data:image/png;base64,). The **Configure Columns **panel appears. For example, for the Electronic Invoicing service:![](data:image/png;base64,)

- Select the checkboxes corresponding to the columns that you wish to display.

- Drag columns to the desired position using the icon ![](data:image/png;base64,).

- Click **Configure** to apply the configuration.

> Important

The columns highlighted by a light blue (preselected) checkbox cannot be disabled or moved.

> Tip

Click **Reset** to reset the default columns and the predefined order.

## Common actions on tables
The table toolbar allows to perform common actions on the displayed data.

- [Sorting data](/doxee-platform/docs/doxee-platform-3-common-functionalities-ei-eo-services-1#sorting-data)

- [Reloading data](/doxee-platform/docs/doxee-platform-3-common-functionalities-ei-eo-services-1#reloading-data)

- [Exporting data](/doxee-platform/docs/doxee-platform-3-common-functionalities-ei-eo-services-1#exporting-data) 

### Sorting data
Click on a column header to sort the data according to the corresponding key.

Click on the column header again to reverse the sort order (ascending or descending)

> Note

The current sorting is highlighted by the icons ![](data:image/png;base64,iVBORw0KGgoAAAANSUhEUgAAAA0AAAAMCAYAAAC5tzfZAAAAe0lEQVQoFb3RQQqAIBAFUO9/K3NjuJQiJBDBEwiz/mEZTJaRmxZuxMcf/wgiQu8RvSC/f0AJ0U2Y1ojUmKJCCcFqKCkhpYK24REyxEFGBxzne2JBHOQED88SayiIanCOdL3nUBAtMM0/MDgYuFLMnvTe1r1NVsT3Jf+HNs1ZSRcC32lMAAAAAElFTkSuQmCC) or ![](data:image/png;base64,iVBORw0KGgoAAAANSUhEUgAAAA0AAAAMCAYAAAC5tzfZAAAAe0lEQVQoFc3QuwqAMAwFUP//rwKlWwUFKXSwQ8Ehe+dIUqUPbcHNIUvDaW4yxRjpa00C0JPdLHnsfND0BR2rJgAgUIZcC9GRUSB9tQRJdU3aadapUcEClO8J8V7YwJAnlIDXyaiFHLcTuUYC+xPuKz+RwPE13xHDQf0cncbPSPz5NLVFAAAAAElFTkSuQmCC) displayed next to the column header.

![](data:image/png;base64,)

### Reloading data
Click ![](data:image/png;base64,) (**Reload**) to reload the data displayed in the table.

### Exporting data 
To export the results returned by a search in CSV or XLS format, follow these steps:

- Click ![](data:image/png;base64,) (**Export**). The **Export Records** window is displayed.![](data:image/png;base64,)

- Select the required export format and click **Export**.

> Important

The maximum number of records that can be exported in each format is as follows:

Format

Max # of records that can be exported

**CSV**

100,000

**XLS**

30,000

## Viewing the details of a record
You can view the details of a record in two different ways:

- Select the checkbox corresponding to the desired record and click ![](data:image/png;base64,). 

- Click on the name of the desired record.

The **Details **panel appears on the right of the component's table. For example: 

![](data:image/png;base64,)
